[1] Cholera - Zimbabwe (Mashonaland West)
Date: Fri 31 Dec 2010
Source: Eyewitness News [edited]
<http://www.eyewitnessnews.co.za/articleprog.aspx?id=56014>


There has been a rise in the number of cholera cases in President
Robert Mugabe's home district in Zvimba in northern Zimbabwe.

This is the worst time of the year for a cholera outbreak, as heavy
rains can spread cholera bacteria through water sources. Health
workers in Zvimba said that locals who should be using chlorine
tablets to protect themselves are refusing to do so because they do
not like the smell.

Up to 69 cholera cases have been detected so far in the Zvimba
district. Two treatment camps have been set up, and the authorities
insist they are much better prepared than they were during the 2008
outbreak.

--
