[5] Diarrhea - Maldives
Date: Sat 25 Dec 2010
Source: Haveeru [edited]
<http://www.haveeru.com.mv/english/details/33995>


The northern islands of the Maldives are experiencing an epidemic
outbreak of diarrhea. An announcement issued by the Centre for
Community Health and Disease Control (CCHDC) said garbage was found on
the beaches of the islands causing a lack of cleanliness and a rapid
increase in the housefly population.

The centre stressed that steps such preventing flies from
contaminating food, drinking chlorinated or boiled water, safe
disposal of garbage, and keeping the islands clean have to be taken to
prevent such diseases.

--
