[6] Diarrhea - Panama
Date: Fri 24 Dec 2010
Source: Prensa Latina [trans. Corr.SB, edited]
<http://www.prensa-latina.cu/index.php?option=3Dcom_content&task=3Dview&i=d=3D249835&Itemid=3D1>


Panama's health authorities are concerned about an increase in
diarrhea cases in recent days, coinciding with measures taken to
prevent cholera. The head of the emergency room in Hospital Santo
Tomas, Nestor Vega, confirmed there had been an increase in the number
of severe acute diarrheal cases in December 2010 attributed to
increased consumption of street food.

Consequently, he added, people should be careful where they eat,
especially now when there is a shortage of drinking water in many
parts of the country. Through November 2010, the Department of
Epidemiology, Ministry of Health had recorded 197 985 cases of acute
diarrhea in the country compared to 164 487 in 2009.

